<h2>The Smiling Boy in the Hallway</h2>
<p>
    When Lina moved into her grandmother’s old apartment, she noticed the hallway outside her room always smelled faintly of smoke after midnight. At first she assumed it came from another tenant, but the odor only appeared near the framed family portraits hanging on the wall. One evening she spotted a young boy standing at the far end of the hallway wearing striped pajamas and smiling at her silently. Thinking he was a neighbor’s child, she greeted him, but he immediately ran toward the dark stairwell without making a sound. The strange thing was that the building had no children living there.
</p>
<br>
<p>
    The next night, Lina woke up to soft footsteps circling her bedroom door. She checked the peephole and saw the same boy standing motionless outside, still smiling. His grin looked unnaturally wide, exposing gums that seemed too dark to be normal. Slowly, he lifted one finger to his lips as if warning her to stay quiet. Then he whispered, “He follows loud people.”
</p>
<br>
<p>
    Moments later, heavy footsteps thundered up the stairwell outside her apartment. The boy’s smile vanished instantly, and he backed away into the darkness. Lina heard a violent pounding on her front door followed by deep breathing from the other side. Terrified, she hid in her closet until sunrise. When she finally opened the door, she discovered long scratch marks carved across the wood and one sentence written in ash on the hallway wall: “The boy can’t protect you twice.”
</p>